HEADWORD: Scarificator
<hw>Scar"i*fi*ca`tor</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>scarificateur</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Surg.)</fld> <def>An instrument,
principally used in cupping, containing several lancets moved
simultaneously by a spring, for making slight incisions.</def>⟦br⟧
